node.text:
Homemade Shui Jiao with a generous amount of filling🥟 Don’t you love it when each dumpling is thick and fat and not stingy on the filling. That’s exactly how I made mine!⁣
⁣
The recipe below has quite a lot of prawns🦐, probably more than the mince meat. Feel free to reduce the amount and add more mince meat instead ❤️⁣
⁣
Ingredients for dumpling:⁣
26 shui jiao round wrapper⁣
Bowl of water (for glueing the sides together)⁣
250g minced pork⁣
19 prawns, chopped into small pieces ⁣
5 shiitake mushrooms, cut into small pieces⁣
2 tbsp corn flour⁣
2 tbsp oyster sauce⁣
2 tsp sesame oil⁣
1 tsp salt⁣
1 tsp sugar⁣
1 tbsp olive oil ⁣
1 tsp ground white pepper⁣
⁣
Steps:⁣
1)Mix all the above ingredients together except the shui jiao wrapper⁣
2)Refrigerate for one hour⁣
3)Place 1 tbsp of filling into the centre of the shui jiao wrapper⁣
4)dap the TOP semi circle of the wrapper with a little water⁣
5)Fold the wrapper into half starting from the bottom until it touches the top until it fully seals the dumpling⁣
6)Use your finger and pinch the sides to create a series of folds (Swipe left to see a video on how I did it)⁣
⁣
